    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Members of a species of beetle, the common name of which reflects that it may infest household larders, feeding upon cheese, dried meats, and raw animal hides; the larva is characterized by short and long reddish-brown or black hair and other distinguishing markings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
